Fiat Spa &lt;FIAT.MI> said it had noplans to issue Eurobonds linked to shares still held by banksafter the placement of the 15 pct Libyan stake in Fiat lastautumn, a company spokesman said.   "An eventual issue of bonds convertible into Fiat shares isnot our responsibility," the spokesman told Reuters. "In case theoperation should be finalized, the bonds would be issued bybanks and not by Fiat, the spokesman said.    The spokesman was commenting on West German press reportsthat Fiat is considering a Eurobond issue of up to 384 mlndlrs, convertible or with warrants attached for exercise intoits shares still held by the banks. REUTER&#3;